---
---

<div>
  <div class="text-center mb-12">
    <span class="eyebrow">What makes DEVS different</span>
    <h2 class="mt-5 text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white">
      A flight simulator for software teams.
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lg copy-muted max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      Not another course. A simulated team environment with the feedback loops, code standards, and dynamics that real jobs throw at you on day one.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-8 text-left">
    <div class="flex gap-5">
      <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-11 h-11 rounded-lg bg-[var(--color-accent)]/10 border border-[var(--color-accent)]/25 flex items-center justify-center">
        <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-[var(--color-accent)]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M4 4v5h.582m15.356 2A8.001 8.001 0 004.582 9m0 0H9m11 11v-5h-.581m0 0a8.003 8.003 0 01-15.357-2m15.357 2H15"/></svg>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">Simulated feedback loops</h3>
        <p class="text-sm copy-muted">Practice the real cycle: get a task, plan, code, open a PR, respond to reviewer feedback, revise, and ship. Over and over until it's muscle memory.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex gap-5">
      <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-11 h-11 rounded-lg bg-[var(--color-accent-2)]/10 border border-[var(--color-accent-2)]/25 flex items-center justify-center">
        <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-[var(--color-accent-2)]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 20h5v-2a3 3 0 00-5.356-1.857M17 20H7m10 0v-2c0-.656-.126-1.283-.356-1.857M7 20H2v-2a3 3 0 015.356-1.857M7 20v-2c0-.656.126-1.283.356-1.857m0 0a5.002 5.002 0 019.288 0M15 7a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0z"/></svg>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">Real teamwork simulation</h3>
        <p class="text-sm copy-muted">Simulated teammates, reviewer personas, standup threads, and sprint ceremonies. Learn to communicate and collaborate, not just code in isolation.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="flex gap-5">
      <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-11 h-11 rounded-lg bg-[var(--color-accent)]/10 border border-[var(--color-accent)]/25 flex items-center justify-center">
        <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-[var(--color-accent)]" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24" aria-hidden="true"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m5.618-4.016A11.955 11.955 0 0112 2.944a11.955 11.955 0 01-8.618 3.04A12.02 12.02 0 003 9c0 5.591 3.824 10.29 9 11.622 5.176-1.332 9-6.03 9-11.622 0-1.042-.133-2.052-.382-3.016z"/></svg>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-2">Real code standards</h3>
        <p class="text-sm copy-muted">Quality gates, lint checks, review rubrics, and definition-of-done requirements. Your code doesn't just run — it has to be mergeable.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
